The paper discusses multi-robot formation control, which is a topic in robotics (cs.RO). The optimization problem and solution method proposed in the paper involve mathematical programming and algorithms, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the theoretical lower bound of formation bias, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and system theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses methods of transformation between different formations, which is a topic in multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
